<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>38-402</num>
  <heading>Control of school construction and repairs.</heading>
  <text>The Director of the Department of Consumer and Regulatory Affairs (“Director”) shall have the same authority, control over, and supervision of the construction or repair of a public school building as the Director has of the construction or repair of any privately owned building.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History" doc="Stat. 45-3-ch182" path="">Mar. 3, 1879, 20 Stat. 408, ch. 182</annotation>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 8-143" type="History">June 22, 1990, D.C. Law 8-143, § 4, 37 DCR 2972</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1973 Ed., § 31-803.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 31-202.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Cross References">Minor repairs by janitors, see <cite path="§38-903">§ 38-903</cite>.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
